Silhouette

A mountainous silhouette emerges against a colorful backdrop of dots.

The code combines Perlin noise to create a mountain-like silhouette and a color gradient using the viridis palette. The points are created within a grid system with their color determined by position. The silhouette is formed by calculating the intersection of polygons.

library(ggplot2)
library(ambient)
library(viridis)
library(sp)

set.seed(0)
y_floor <- -10
grid_size <- 70
x_range <- c(-10, 10)
y_range <- c(y_floor, 10)

x <- rep(seq(x_range[1], x_range[2], length.out = grid_size), each = grid_size)
y <- rep(seq(y_range[1], y_range[2], length.out = grid_size), grid_size)
df <- data.frame(x = x, y = y, color = cos(atan2(y, x) + sqrt(x^2 + y^2) / 10))

n_silhouette <- 10000
x_silhouette <- seq(x_range[1] - 1, x_range[2] + 1, length.out = n_silhouette)
noise <- noise_perlin(c(n_silhouette, 1), frequency = 3/n_silhouette, octaves = 3) * 2
silhouette_df <- data.frame(x = x_silhouette, y = 20 * abs(noise) + y_floor - 0.1)

inside_silhouette <- point.in.polygon(df$x, df$y, silhouette_df$x, silhouette_df$y)
df$color[inside_silhouette == 1] <- NA

ggplot() +
    geom_point(data = df, aes(x = x, y = y, color = color), shape = 20, fill = "white", size = 2) +
    scale_color_gradientn(colors = rev(viridis(100, 1, 0.3, 1.0)), na.value = "white") +
    theme_void() +
    theme(legend.position = "none")
